Sentencas: (La0.6Ba0.4)(CO0.2Fe0.8)O-3 (LBCF) is synthesized by a sol-gel method as a Cr-tolerant cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (ITSOFCs).
Titulo: Characterization and performance of (La,Ba)(Co,Fe)O3 cathode for solid oxide fuel cells with iron-chromium metallic interconnect

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance and Cr deposition process for the O-2 reduction reaction on LBCF cathodes in the presence and absence of a Fe-Cr alloy interconnect are investigated in detail, in comparison with a (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O-3 (LSCF) electrode.
Titulo: Characterization and performance of (La,Ba)(Co,Fe)O3 cathode for solid oxide fuel cells with iron-chromium metallic interconnect

Sentencas: Cr deposition occurs for the 02 reduction reaction on LBCF electrodes in the presence of Fe-Cr alloy.
Titulo: Characterization and performance of (La,Ba)(Co,Fe)O3 cathode for solid oxide fuel cells with iron-chromium metallic interconnect

Sentencas: Very different from that observed for the reaction on the LSCF cathode, Cr deposition on the LBCF electrode/gadolinia-doped ceria (CDC) electrolyte system is very small and shows little poisoning effect for O-2 reduction on LBCF electrode.
Titulo: Characterization and performance of (La,Ba)(Co,Fe)O3 cathode for solid oxide fuel cells with iron-chromium metallic interconnect

Sentencas: The results demonstrate that the LBCF electrode has a high resistance towards Cr deposition and high tolerance towards Cr poisoning.
Titulo: Characterization and performance of (La,Ba)(Co,Fe)O3 cathode for solid oxide fuel cells with iron-chromium metallic interconnect
